---
import MainLayout from '../../../layouts/MainLayout.astro';
import MotuSidebar from '../../../components/MotuSidebar.astro';
const title = "CueMix FX Software";
---
<MainLayout title={title}>
  <div class="flex gap-8 items-start">
    <div class="w-[250px] flex-shrink-0">
      <MotuSidebar />
    </div>
    <article class="prose max-w-none">
      <h1>{title}</h1>
      <p>Source: <a href="https://motu.com/products/motuaudio/ultralite-mk3/cuemix-fx-overview.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener">MOTU product page</a></p>

      <p>CueMix FX is MOTU's control software that exposes the full DSP mixer, routing matrix, and hardware effects in a single tabbed interface. All settings made in CueMix FX are stored in the MOTU's internal flash memory and persist even when the computer is off.</p>

      <h2>Main Interface Tabs</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Mix tab:</strong> the main mixing pane. Each input appears as a mixer strip with fader, mute, and pan. Assign any input to any output bus. Configure multiple parallel monitor mixes (Mix 1, Mix 2, etc.) simultaneously from one screen.</li>
        <li><strong>EQ tab:</strong> graphic parametric EQ editor with a visual frequency curve. Click and drag individual band handles directly on the curve. Apply the 7-band Modeled EQ to any input or bus independently.</li>
        <li><strong>Dynamics tab:</strong> access the hardware LA-2A Leveler and Conventional Compressor. Set threshold, ratio, attack, release, and makeup gain per channel.</li>
        <li><strong>Reverb tab:</strong> configure the onboard Classic Reverb — room type, size, pre-delay, decay, diffusion. Route inputs to the reverb via send knobs in the Mix tab.</li>
        <li><strong>Analysis tab:</strong> real-time metering tools — FFT spectrum display, spectrogram waterfall, oscilloscope, X-Y Lissajous plot, and phase meter.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Saving Session Presets</h2>
      <p>Use File → Save As in CueMix FX to save a complete routing and effects snapshot as a named preset. Create separate presets for: recording session (minimal latency, direct monitoring), mixing session (full bus routing, effects active), and live performance (standalone mode layout).</p>

      <figure>
        <img src="https://cdn-data.motu.com/site/images/cuemix-fx/mix_large.jpg" alt="CueMix FX mixer interface" />
        <figcaption>Official MOTU-hosted CueMix FX image.</figcaption>
      </figure>
    </article>
  </div>
</MainLayout>
